h3. Summary
Editing a multi-user picker field for an issue via  */rest/api/3/issue/{issueId}* does not work when using accountId.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Make a *PUT* request to */rest/api/3/issue/{issueId}* containing the following JSON body where custom field ID is for a multi-user picker type field: 
{code:json}
{
    "fields": {
        "customfield_10055": [
            {
                "accountId": "0f0000fff0ffff0f0000f00f"
            }
        ]
    }
}
{code} 
# Get HTTP response code 204.
# Check the issue in the Jira UI.

h3. Expected Results
The multi-user picker custom field has been updated to include the specified user. 

h3. Actual Results
No values have been added to the multi-user custom field. 
 
h3. Notes
accountId is working for single user picker custom field type. 

h3. Workaround
Currently the name parameter is supported, this would be the username of the user you wish to add like below: 
{code:json}
{
    "fields": {
        "customfield_10055": [
            {
                "name": "admin"
            }
        ]
    }
}
{code}

h3. Summary

The new view doesn't accept format text (italic, bold, etc) if there is a text with a hard break (shift+enter).
h3. Environment

Jira Cloud
h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # try to update/ insert a text in a comment or description with a hard break (shift+enter) and any format text (italic, bold, etc).
 # Save changes.

h3. Expected Results

The changes will be saved.
h3. Actual Results

!Screen Shot 2019-05-06 at 12.43.19.png|thumbnail!

In my analyze, I could identify that the Jira is applying the formatted text on the hard break and this is possibly causing the problem.

!Screen Shot 2019-05-06 at 12.46.33.png|thumbnail!
{code:java}
{
  "version": 1,
  "type": "doc",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "test",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "hardBreak",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "test2",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "strong"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}{code}
h3. Workaround
 # Remove formatting (eg. bold, italic, underline) from end of line and then use shift+enter
or
 # Use just enter instead of shift+enter.

h3. Summary
Transitioning an issue via */rest/api/3/issue/ \{issueid}/transitions* clears data such as summary if these fields are not provided in the REST call.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
 # Add a screen to a transition
 # Make a call to */rest/api/3/issue/ \{issueid}/transitions* to transition an issue with field updates like below:
{code}
{
    "transition": {
        "id": 21
    },
    "fields": {
        "description": {
            "version": 1,
            "type": "doc",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "this is my description now"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "customfield_10054": "http://www.ramblingvapers.com",        
        "customfield_10051": {
            "version": 1,
            "type": "doc",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "root cause"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "customfield_10052": {
            "version": 1,
            "type": "doc",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "some text"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "customfield_10053": {
            "version": 1,
            "type": "doc",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "texty text"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }        
    }
}
{code}
# Make a further call to transition again:
{code}
{
    "transition": {
        "id": 11
    }
}
{code}


h3. Expected Results
The field values remain the same
h3. Actual Results
The field values such as Description are cleared.

h3. Workaround

Currently the best workaround is to use the API V2 endpoint: [The Jira Cloud platform REST API V2: Transition Issue|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v2/#api-rest-api-2-issue-issueIdOrKey-transitions-post]

h3. Summary
Updating issue values such as description or custom fields is not working as expected:
# The history tab is not handling the ADF and displaying the full json content of the response. 
# Custom field values are not populated correctly. 
# The jiraissuetokens table is not being updated meaning values populated are not searchable. 

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Add a screen to a transition
# Make a call to */rest/api/3/issue/{issueid}/transitions* to transition an issue with field updates like below:
{code:json}
{
    "transition": {
        "id": 21
    },
    "fields": {
        "description": {
            "version": 1,
            "type": "doc",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "this is my description now"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "customfield_10054": "http://www.ramblingvapers.com",        
        "customfield_10051": {
            "version": 1,
            "type": "doc",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "root cause"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "customfield_10052": {
            "version": 1,
            "type": "doc",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "some text"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "customfield_10053": {
            "version": 1,
            "type": "doc",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                        {
                            "type": "text",
                            "text": "texty text"
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }        
    }
}
{code}

h3. Expected Results
The custom field values are populated correctly.
The values are included in the *jiraissuetokens* table. 
This history displays the values correctly:
 !screenshot-2.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Actual Results
The custom field values are not populated correctly or at all.
The values are not added to the *jiraissuetokens* table. 
This history displays full ADF json:
 !screenshot-1.png|thumbnail! 

h3. Workaround
Currently the best workaround is to use the API V2 endpoint: [The Jira Cloud platform REST API V2: Transition Issue|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v2/#api-rest-api-2-issue-issueIdOrKey-transitions-post]
